Implementation Plan - Chicago IT Specialist Portfolio
Creating a premium, modern portfolio website for an IT specialist targeting Chicago-based businesses and buildings.

Proposed Changes
Tech Stack
Structure: Semantic HTML5
Styling: Vanilla CSS (Modern CSS features: Grid, Flexbox, Custom Properties)
Logic: Vanilla JavaScript
Animations: CSS Transitions & Intersection Observer API
Design System
Color Palette:
Primary: #0A192F (Deep Navy - Professional/Trust)
Accent: #64FFDA (Cyan/Teal - High Tech/Action)
Secondary: #112240 (Slate Blue - Depth)
Text: #CCD6F6 (Light Silver - Readability)
Typography:
Headings: 'Inter', sans-serif (Bold, Modern)
Body: 'Roboto Mono', monospace (Technical feel)
[NEW] Assets
hero-chicago.jpg: A stunning Chicago skyline at night with subtle digital network overlays.
service-networking.jpg: Close-up of high-quality networking cables/servers.
service-security.jpg: Modern security dashboard/monitoring interface.
service-support.jpg: IT specialist assisting a client in a modern office environment.
[NEW] 
index.html
Main entry point with semantic HTML5 sections: Header, Hero, Services, Portfolio, Testimonials (Chicago focused), and Contact.
[NEW] 
style.css
Global styles, typography, and responsive layout.
Glassmorphism effects for cards and headers.
[NEW] 
main.js
Smooth scrolling, scroll-triggered animations, and contact form handling.
Verification Plan
Automated Tests
Run npm run dev to check for build errors.
Use the browser tool to verify layout on Desktop and Mobile.
Manual Verification
Check all links and hover states.
Verify the "Chicago Focus" is prominent in the copy and imagery.